# Tailwind Styling Guide for Digital Signage Website

This rule documents the custom Tailwind CSS configuration and usage conventions for the digital signage SaaS project. The configuration is defined in [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js).

---

## 🎨 Color System

- **Primary Palette:** Custom purple and pink shades for branding and accents.
- **Gray Scale:** Extended with `gray-750`, `gray-850`, and `gray-950` for nuanced dark backgrounds.
- **Semantic Colors:** `background` and `accent` color objects for main backgrounds and highlights.

### Usage Examples
```html
<!-- Main backgrounds -->
<div class="bg-gray-900">Dark background</div>
<div class="bg-gray-850">Custom darker shade</div>

<!-- Accent colors -->
<span class="text-purple-400">Purple text</span>
<button class="bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-500">Purple button</button>
<div class="bg-linear-to-r from-purple-600 to-pink-600">Gradient background</div>
```

---

## 🖋️ Typography
- **Font Families:** Uses `Inter var` for sans and `Lexend` for display.
- **Headings:** White by default, with accent options.
- **Body:** `text-gray-300` for regular text, `text-white` for emphasis.

```html
<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">Heading</h2>
<p class="text-gray-300">Body text</p>
<span class="text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-linear-to-r from-purple-400 to-pink-600">Gradient text</span>
```

---

## 🟪 Cards & Containers
- **Rounded corners:** Use `rounded-2xl`, `rounded-3xl`, etc.
- **Shadows:** Use `shadow-lg`, `shadow-glow-purple`, etc.
- **Rings:** Use `ring-1 ring-gray-700/10` for subtle borders.

```html
<div class="rounded-2xl bg-gray-800 p-8 shadow-lg ring-1 ring-gray-700/10">Card content</div>
<div class="rounded-3xl bg-gray-800 p-8 hover:bg-gray-700/70 hover:ring-purple-500 transition-all duration-300">Interactive card</div>
```

---

## 🫧 Floating & Backdrop Blur
- Use `backdrop-blur-sm` or custom blur utilities for glassmorphism effects.

```html
<div class="rounded-2xl bg-purple-500/10 backdrop-blur-sm p-6 shadow-lg ring-1 ring-purple-500/20">Floating content</div>
```

---

## 🔘 Buttons
- **Primary:** Gradient backgrounds, rounded-full, bold text.
- **Secondary:** Text buttons with group hover effects.

```html
<button class="rounded-full bg-linear-to-r from-purple-600 to-pink-600 px-6 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:opacity-90 transition-all duration-300">Gradient Button</button>
<button class="text-sm font-semibold leading-6 text-white group">Text Button <span class="inline-block transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-1">→</span></button>
```

---

## ✨ Special Effects
- **Animated elements:** Use `animate-float`, `animate-pulse-slow` for floating/pulse effects.
- **Gradient blobs:** Use absolute, blurred, and clipped divs for background art.

```html
<div class="animate-float">Floating element</div>
<div class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-green-400 animate-pulse-slow"></div>
```

---

## 📝 Form Elements
- **Inputs:** Use `bg-white/5`, `ring-1 ring-inset ring-white/10`, `text-white` for dark forms.
- **Checkboxes:** Use `bg-gray-900`, `text-purple-600`, `focus:ring-purple-600`.

```html
<input type="text" class="block w-full rounded-md border-0 bg-white/5 px-3.5 py-2 text-white shadow-sm ring-1 ring-inset ring-white/10 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-inset focus:ring-purple-500 sm:text-sm sm:leading-6">
<input type="checkbox" class="h-4 w-4 rounded border-gray-700 bg-gray-900 text-purple-600 focus:ring-purple-600">
```

---

## 📱 Responsive Design
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) for grid, text, and padding.

```html
<div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">...</div>
<p class="text-sm sm:text-base lg:text-lg">Responsive text</p>
<div class="p-4 sm:p-6 lg:p-8">Responsive padding</div>
```

---

## 🛠️ Custom Utilities & Plugins
- **Shadows:** `shadow-glow-purple`, `shadow-glow-pink` for accent glows.
- **Border radius:** Up to `rounded-4xl` for pill/soft cards.
- **Animations:** `pulse-slow`, `float` for subtle motion.
- **Typography plugin:** For rich text content.
- **Forms plugin:** For consistent form styling.
- **Aspect-ratio plugin:** For media and embeds.

---

## 🧑‍💻 Developer Notes
- Always use Tailwind utilities for styling; avoid custom CSS unless necessary.
- Support both light and dark mode using `dark:` variants.
- Reference [tailwind.config.js](mdc:tailwind.config.js) for all available custom tokens and utilities.
- Test all UI in both light and dark themes for accessibility and contrast.
